# SOUL.md

This file gives heartbeat-gateway context about what the agent is currently
working on. The classifier reads three sections: Current Phase, Autonomy
Boundaries, and Active Decisions.

## Current Phase

Phase 3: Webhook Adapter Implementation
Goal: Implement and test Linear, GitHub, and PostHog webhook adapters.
Active branch: feature/webhook-adapters
Timeline: Current sprint

## Autonomy Boundaries

- May create files in heartbeat_gateway/ and tests/
- May run pytest and ruff
- May NOT push to main without explicit approval
- May NOT modify pyproject.toml dependencies without discussion
- Escalate to human if: CI is broken on main, a dependency has a breaking change

## Active Decisions

- ADR-001: Using LiteLLM as provider interface (model-agnostic)
- ADR-002: Async background classification (return 200 immediately)
- ADR-003: HEARTBEAT.md as the only persistent state (no database)
